When there are 16 trillion billionaires, do we still try to redistribute the trillionaires wealth? 

@peterrhague walked us through the space math. 16 Trillion people could materially consume billionaire level energy (planes, yachts, etc) and we'd still have room to growth 1000X before we exhausted the suns energy. 

And you're squabbling over whether or not SpaceX (who has uncontested access to this energy) might be worth more than earths GDP?

